Vedanta Zambian Unit Considering Lusaka Exchange Listing, Daily Mail Says

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-06-14T12:04:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/vedanta-zambian-unit-considering-lusaka-exchange-listing-daily-mail-says.html
Konkola Copper Mines Plc, the
Zambian unit of  Vedanta Resources Plc (VED) , is considering selling
shares on the country’s stock exchange, the Daily Mail reported,
without saying where it got the information.  This follows the decision by First Quantum Minerals Ltd. to
list on the Lusaka Stock Exchange, the state-controlled
newspaper reported.  Vedanta hasn’t yet decided on a listing in Lusaka or
 London , Konkola said in an e-mailed response to questions today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka at 
 amukwita1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  